Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450}(chopped into 2cm wide wedges, no need to peel) into wedges. Pop the wedges onto a #large, low-sided, wide baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{for roasting}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the wedges nicely spread out.

Put the @garlic salt{1} into a #large bowl{}. Add the @panko breadcrumbs{10} and @water{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then add the @British beef mince{240}. Mix with your hands until well combined. Roll the mince into even-sized balls then flatten to make burger patties 1cm thick (1 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Pop the burgers on a #baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, chop the @medium tomato{1}(chopped into 2cm pieces) into pieces. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then separate the leaves. Put the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing) into a #medium bowl{}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}. Mix together and add the tomatoes, stir to combine and set aside.

> TIP: We'll add the lettuce later to avoid it wilting.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30} and @red leicester{30}.

Once the burgers and wedges are cooked, transfer your potatoes to the bottom of your oven. Remove the burgers from your oven and carefully pile the cheese on top of them, followed by the @BBQ sauce{32}. Turn your oven to grill setting, pop your burgers back into your oven under the grill and cook until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop the @glazed burger buns{2} on the middle shelf of your oven. Warm for ~{2-3%minutes}. Serve the burgers and a couple of lettuce leaves per person in your buns. Add the remaining lettuce to the dressing and toss to coat (or leave some salad undressed if the kids don't want it). Serve the salad and potato wedges alongside the burgers and enjoy!